{
  "texts": [
    "Results are shown in Figure 6 and based on LLama3 on TREC.",
    "We report, for each sample, its sensitivity and the average consistency against all other samples of the same class.",
    "These results clearly show that our choice of Q = 30 produces a much different distribution of points compared to the perturbed versions of the LLM.",
    "Note, however, that Q = 30 is not high enough to distinguish random consistency values from LLama3 in the specific case of TREC, since sampling is not perfectly uniform.",
    "That said, if observed jointly with sensitivity, a clear picture emerges."
  ]
}